  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db8\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dba \u0dba\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dbb\u0dda\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dbb\u0ddc\u0d9a\u0da7\u0dca \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0d9a \u0db4\u0daf\u0dca\u0db0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dbd\u0db6\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Germany gives Ukraine a missile defense system",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The third of Germany's Mars-II multiple launch rocket systems (MLRS) has arrived in Ukraine, the country's Defense Minister, Alexei Reznikov, has announced.",
        "\u201cThe third brother of the Longhand family, Germany's MLRS MARS II has arrived in Ukraine. Thanks to Germany and personally to my colleague the Minister of Defense for these systems. Our artillerymen will salute our German partners, the minister tweeted.",
        "The Mars-II is a German, Italian and French-developed modification of the US-made MLRS M270 multiple rocket launcher. According to German company KMW, the system's manufacturer, the Mars-II is capable of firing up to 12 missiles per minute at a range of more than 70 km. These missiles can be guided using GPS or mine-clearing missiles."
      ],
